Holograph is based on Propagator Networks, who were discovered and written about by Gerald Sussman and Alexey Radul. They described "a flexible and expressive substrate for computation". Each propagator ideally runs completely independently of each other. It's effectively a massively parallel and distributable computational system, and it just so happens to translate to visual systems beautifully.
